				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/jacob-conwell" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1372582); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1372582&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610204704" alt="Jacob Conwell" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1372582)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/jacob-conwell" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1372582); return false;" >Jacob Conwell</a></span> <span class="odate time_1456992903 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">03 Mar 2016 08:15</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2466809">
									

<p>There have been few things on this site that have switched between boring and entertaining as much as this AAR.</p>
<p>Echoing what others have said, the technobabble about the Paratech in the first section is pretty hit and miss. Some objects are interesting to read about, others made my eyes glaze over. None of this was enough to convince me to stop reading, as the interesting tech was particularly interesting.</p>
<p>On a different note, there is a fair amount of blacking out in this, and I am a little puzzled as to why. A rule of thumb that I have is that there should be a rather inherent reason (which the reader should guess) as to why information is being removed. For the location, I could guess that the higher ranks don't want the reader to poke around the mission location, which is fine. As for that first date, I am lost as to why that needed to be blacked out.</p>
<p>Getting into the description of the event, I felt like it played out very much like a fast paced action movie at some parts, and slowed to a crawl at others, which made the flow kind of choppy.</p>
<p>Overall, +1. While a good chunk of this is drier than the Sahara, the parts that are interesting and work are very interesting and work well.</p>

							</div>

								
					
