		<div class="post" id="post-2466937">
		<div class="long">
			<div class="head">
									<div class="options">
						<a href="javascript:;" onclick="togglePostFold(event,2466937)" class="btn btn-default btn-small btn-sm">Fold</a>
					</div>
								<div class="title" id="post-title-2466937">
																		
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/sirpudding" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(348648); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=348648&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610204704" alt="sirpudding" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=348648)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/sirpudding" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(348648); return false;" >sirpudding</a></span> <span class="odate time_1457016524 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">03 Mar 2016 14:48</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2466937">
									

<blockquote>
<p>There have been few things on this site that have switched between boring and entertaining as much as this AAR.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Well, I guess I aim to be unique.</p>
<p>I was concerned about it being too dry, but I enjoy reading these things in real life (at least those involving interesting actions) and have written reports that contributed to real ones too. I cut a lot of corners here for entertainment purposes, and I don't think that I would have been personally comfortable with much less authenticity here.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;How&nbsp;the&nbsp;sausage&nbsp;was&nbsp;made</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;And&nbsp;knowing&nbsp;is&nbsp;half&nbsp;the&nbsp;battle!&nbsp;GI&nbsp;Joe!</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<blockquote>
<p>Echoing what others have said, the technobabble about the Paratech in the first section is pretty hit and miss. Some objects are interesting to read about, others made my eyes glaze over. None of this was enough to convince me to stop reading, as the interesting tech was particularly interesting.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>That went through a few variations when writing this, but ultimately, if Tau-5 is tasked with testing this stuff, some detail probably makes sense here. I honestly don't know which items make your eyes glaze over, all of these items were fun to invent and I tried to keep to a short list that fit the threat profile &#8212; that would still seem like enough of a force multiplier to make the four man &quot;squad&quot; that my teammates insisted on viable (essentially this organization is treating them more like IFVs than individual infantrymen, and they needed the survibility to match).</p>
<blockquote>
<p>On a different note, there is a fair amount of blacking out in this, and I am a little puzzled as to why.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Entirely meta reasons, I am afraid.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>For the location, I could guess that the higher ranks don't want the reader to poke around the mission location, which is fine.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>The real reason is that with the short deadline, I really didn't have time to poke around extensively in satellite photos and write the operation around a real building.</p>
<p>It should be somewhere around 29RPQ1926394068, though.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>As for that first date, I am lost as to why that needed to be blacked out.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>That is entirely an oversight, I had meant to fill that in as we got the timeline worked out, but forgot. I'll find out if fixing this is within the contest rules.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Getting into the description of the event, I felt like it played out very much like a fast paced action movie at some parts, and slowed to a crawl at others, which made the flow kind of choppy.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Well, that is combat: periods of intense boredom punctuated by terror. Earlier versions had even more &quot;boring&quot; stuff, but I was eventually persuaded to cut them. Short of ignoring vital operational details (making Hughes look incompetent) or having them teleport into position, or just writing this like the world according to Michael Bay, I don't think that I could really cut much more.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<blockquote>
<p>While a good chunk of this is drier than the Sahara</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Perhaps appropriate given the location&#8230;</p>
<p>ETA: Edits were approved and made! Dates filled along with the MGRS map reference.</p>

							</div>

								
