														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2467215">
									

<p>As in their first story, this reminded me heavily of games (In this case, SCP-themed Darkest Dungeon).</p>
<p>This is clearly a different kind of Foundation (and world) than the one many of the stories are set in, with an almost World of Darkness-y secret but open warfare feeling instead of a mostly normal world with terrifying but often subtle, local or missable phenomena that need to be contained. Under these conditions, the other documents make a lot more sense, especially Avatara's &quot;we found four SCPs. Let's use them in the field!&quot; - I think my opinion of the whole set of articles was lifted by this one.</p>

							</div>

								
					
